We often like to take the inside function as our substitution, in this case \textcolor{red}{u=1-x^2}, so \textcolor{blue}{\dee{u}=-2x\dee{x}}. This takes care of part of the integral:


\int_0^1 (1-2x)\sqrt{\textcolor{red}{1-x^2}}\dee{x}&=
